com.camsolute.code.camp.lib.models

Class CampInstance

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camsolute.code.camp.lib.models.CampInstance
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serialization<CampInstance>, CampInstanceInterface

    public class CampInstance
extends java.lang.Object
implements CampInstanceInterface
    The CampInstance object encapsulates a unique temporal aspect of an object instance at a point in its life cycle. ( together with its process related status aspects.) The temporal aspect of an object instance is denoted by a unique identifier - the objects InstanceId - which changes each time an object is modified or changes state, and is then persisted. (The process status aspect is relevant to any process connected to a business object.) A CampInstance object therefore provides access to a representation of an object at the time it was persisted. In order to be able to navigate the various temporal aspects of an object the CampInstance object contains an object's initial and current InstanceId. NOTE: These aspects are in-transient in nature and must therefore be persisted so that their current (and past) values can exist across both inactive and active life-cycle periods of the business object they are associated with. Inactive life-cycle periods denote those time periods in which only a persisted representation of current (and past) object states exist. Active life-cycle periods of an object denote those time periods in which a runtime representation of the object (object instance) exists within the system.
    Author:
    Christopher Campbell

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      static class  CampInstance.Status
      Status common to all object instances.
      These are:

      CREATED := the object instance is newly created and has not been submitted to any process (can trigger process notification)
      SUBMITTED := the object instance has been submitted to a process (must trigger process notification)
      REJECTED := the object instance has been rejected by a process (must trigger process notification)
      UPDATED := object instance data has been updated (must trigger process notification)
      CANCELED := the main object instance process has been canceled (must trigger process notification)
      FULFILLED := the main object instance process has completed successfully (must trigger process notification)
      MODIFIED := [system use] object instance data has been modified, the system needs to be informed, the status at modification time is stacked (previous status)
      CLEAN := [system use] the system has acted on modified status, the previous status is popped from stack and status CLEAN is pushed to stack.
      DIRTY := [system use] a displayable object instance's display needs to be updated
